oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Performance - Fiddle Demonstration - 2016-07-31
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Fiddle instrument demonstration by Buddy Spicher, Billy Contreras, Matthew Spicher and David Spicher from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on July 31, 2016. In support of the exhibit Dylan, Cash, and the Nashville Cats: A New Music City.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Buddy Spicher; Matthew Spicher; David Spicher; Billy Contreras;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Includes questions from the audience. Performance include; Jesse Polka -- Medley (Unidentified/Little Pals Train/Nashville Swing Band) -- Sugarfoot Rag -- The Gal I Left Behind Me (David Spicher and Wendy Newcomer on vocals) -- Bonaparte's Retreat (Andrea Ladd on vocals) -- New San Antonio Rose -- Maiden's Prayer -- Sally Goodin (Billy Contreras) - My Window Faces The South (Matthew Spicher on vocals) -- It Wasn't God Who Made Honky Tonk Angels (Wendy Newcomer) -- Right Or Wrong (Wendy Newcomer on vocals) -- Unidentified Hoedown (Billy Contreras) -- Little Rock Getaway -- Air Mail Special.
